The global Fourier Transform Infrared (FTIR) portable spectrometer market is expected to witness significant growth in the coming years. The market is driven by the increasing demand for portable and easy-to-use spectroscopy solutions across various industries such as pharmaceuticals, food and beverages, environmental analysis, and more. The rising need for rapid and accurate analysis tools for quality control, material identification, and contamination analysis is propelling the adoption of FTIR portable spectrometers. Moreover, technological advancements in spectrometry, such as improved resolution and sensitivity, are further boosting market growth.

In terms of product segmentation, the market is divided into handheld spectrometers and microscope spectrometers. Handheld spectrometers are gaining popularity due to their compact size, portability, and ease of use, making them ideal for on-site analysis in diverse industries. On the other hand, microscope spectrometers offer higher magnification capabilities, making them suitable for analyzing small samples or surfaces with precision. The versatility of portable FTIR spectrometers in meeting the varying needs of end-users is expected to drive market expansion.

